			<title><![CDATA[October '14 Release Thread]]></title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?77284-October-14-Release-Thread&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Tue, 30 Sep 2014 19:04:10 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[October is traditionally one of the months with the highest volume of new games, so bear with me as I attempt to highlight a few dozen things you might want to know about. The biggest game this month was going to be Assassin's Creed, but it apparently got delayed to November, which leaves us...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>October is traditionally one of the months with the highest volume of new games, so bear with me as I attempt to highlight a few dozen things you might want to know about. The biggest game this month was going to be Assassin's Creed, but it apparently got delayed to November, which leaves us without an obvious heavyweight this month. <br />
<br />
I guess the first thing I will mention is <b>Alien: Isolation</b>. They promise they are doing it right this time. I don't know if the game will be good, but at the very least, they are making it about a single Alien that you cannot kill and have to escape from. Like Borderlands? There's more <b>Borderlands</b>, in <b>The Pre-Sequel</b>. Play as characters aligned with Handsome Jack from Borderlands 2 before he went evil and bounce around on the moon. Note that this is made by another studio as Gearbox presumably works on Borderlands 3.<br />
<br />
If you are up for something spooky this month, <b>The Evil Within</b> might be up your alley. This is the survival horror that is supposed to bring survival horror back, as opposed to the action games all the others have become lately. Maybe you want to tone down the scares but still want a Halloween themed game to enjoy this month? <b>Costume Quest 2</b> is also due this month. This is the cartoony rpg from Double Fine in which you play as kids trick or treating. <br />
<br />
The PC is getting <b>Civilization: Beyond Earth</b>, as well as a port of the Xone's <b>Ryse</b> (apparently), and <b>Final Fantasy 13</b>. Apparently Square is planning on releasing FF13-2 and FF13-3 on PC too, so all you PC gamers can be in just as much agony as the rest of us! Seriously though, they are launching it at $15, which is amazing for various reasons, and probably a litmus test for whether or not they will bother porting FF15 to PC.<br />
<br />
The Xone has a good month for exclusives, with <b>Project Overdrive</b> leading the charge. This is the kind of silly third person shooter from the Ratchet and Clank guys. The Kinect game based on <b>Fantasia</b> and made by the Dance Central guys is also due soon. The PS4's big exclusive this month is <b>Driveclub</b>. The Wii U meanwhile gets <b>Bayonetta 2</b>. <br />
<br />
On handhelds, the 3DS gets its version of <b>Smash Bros</b> as well as <b>Fantasy Life</b>, an rpg from Level 5 (Ni No Kuni). The Vita is finally getting <b>Freedom Wars</b>, that monster hunter looking game I posted about a long time ago with the sci-fi anime theme of having to fight monsters to pay off a prison sentence.<br />
<br />
That's not all, be sure to check the spoiler for the complete list, and share anything I missed.<br />
<br />
